# Image size & compression policy

Canonical constants live in `lib/image-size-policy.ts`. Processing is in `lib/media-process.ts`.

## Rules

1. **Gallery / content images** — full quality allowed up to **500 KB**.
2. **Hero images** — full quality allowed up to **800 KB**.
3. **Only compress when the source file is above 1 MB.**
   - At or under 1 MB: orientation-only pass-through (no lossy re-encode).
   - Over 1 MB: lossy WebP compression aimed at the kind’s target (800 KB heroes, 500 KB gallery/content).

## Do

- Pass `imageKind` (`hero` | `gallery` | `content`) through admin upload when known.
- Use `shouldCompressImage()` / `processImageToWebp(buf, { kind })` — do not hardcode quality or always-compress in new upload paths.
- Keep signed-upload of originals for files ≤ 1 MB; route > 1 MB through the processing upload API.

## Don’t

- Don’t reintroduce blanket WebP q82/q88 compression for every upload.
- Don’t compress email-template images with this policy unless explicitly requested (separate 5 MB email limits).
- Don’t “upscale” or invent resolution; max edge applies only when compressing oversized sources.
